<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="or-conj">or <strong><em>conj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ɔː(r)/    美 /ɔːr/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>[表示选择] 或者；还是：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Which do you prefer, white, grey or brown?
你喜欢哪种颜色，白色、灰色还是褐色?</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>[表示不明确] 大约：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>two or three miles
两三英里</p></div>

<h4 id="3-else">3.★ <strong>[常与else连用] 否则；要不然：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Hurry up, <strong>or</strong> ( <strong>else</strong> ) you’ll be late for school.
快点，否则你上学会迟到的。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>[用以引导同义词或同义语] 或者说；即：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It’s 10 kilometres, or 20 li, from here to the city.
从这儿到城里有10公里，也就是20里。</p></div>

<h4 id="5">5.★ <strong>[用于否定句] 也不：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He never smokes or drinks.
他从不吸烟，也从不喝酒。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>They kept their collection at home until it got too big<strong><em>_</em></strong>_ until they died.  （2020山东）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. or  </p></div>